Dr. Claude Phipps, SB MIT 61, SM MIT 63, received his Ph.D. from Stanford University in 1972. He developed the ORION concept while a senior R&amp;D staff member at Los Alamos National Labs. He has numerous publications, including 31 invited presentations and a technical book chapter, on laser-surface interactions, laser system design and plasma physics. He presently heads a consulting firm, Photonic Associates of Santa Fe.<br>
